OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1773144740
OL,3,CMental health charity secures funding
OL,4,Cto repair storm-damaged building
OL,6,FA mental health charity that was
OL,7,Fforced to close its doors after their
OL,8,Fbuilding's roof was "wrecked" by
OL,9,Fsevere storms is set to reopen thanks
OL,10,Fto a major funding boost.
OL,12,FCounselling In The Community (CITC)
OL,13,Fhas been awarded #40,000 to complete
OL,14,Furgent structural repairs at its
OL,15,FWaterloo Road site in South Shore.
OL,17,FIn a further move to secure the
OL,18,Fcharity's long-term future, an
OL,19,Fadditional #100,000 has been earmarked
OL,20,Fto allow the organisation to purchase
OL,21,Fthe premises outright.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/7
